Note:
This file handles core MIR (Mid-level Intermediate Representation) type definitions and data structures.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process core MIR type definitions and MIR data structure management
- Handle MIR instruction types and MIR basic block types
- Manage MIR SSA form types and MIR phi node types
- Process MIR control flow types and MIR dominance types

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Core MIR types enable SSA form and control flow graph representation
- Proper MIR type handling ensures correct MIR data structure management
- Core MIR types support enables Runa compilation for SSA-based optimization

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Core MIR type definitions and MIR data structure management
- MIR instruction types and MIR basic block types
- MIR SSA form types and MIR phi node types
- MIR control flow types and MIR dominance types

Dependencies:
- Imports HIR types for type information reuse
- Imports memory/layout.runa for OWNED HEAP allocation (Tier 3)
- Imports collections/list.runa for instruction and value management
- Imports core/string_core.runa for debug printing
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dictionary
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MIR Instruction Opcode Constants (20000-20999)
Note: Mid-level IR uses SSA form with explicit control flow via basic blocks
Note: All operations are platform-agnostic and optimized for analysis
Note: ============================================================================

Note: Arithmetic Operations (20000-20099)
Constant MIR_NOP as Integer is 20000                  Note: No operation
Constant MIR_CONST as Integer is 20001                Note: Constant value
Constant MIR_ADD as Integer is 20002                  Note: Integer/float addition
Constant MIR_SUB as Integer is 20003                  Note: Integer/float subtraction
Constant MIR_MUL as Integer is 20004                  Note: Integer/float multiplication
Constant MIR_DIV as Integer is 20005                  Note: Integer/float division
Constant MIR_MOD as Integer is 20006                  Note: Integer modulo
Constant MIR_NEG as Integer is 20007                  Note: Unary negation
Constant MIR_AND as Integer is 20010                  Note: Bitwise AND
Constant MIR_OR as Integer is 20011                   Note: Bitwise OR
Constant MIR_XOR as Integer is 20012                  Note: Bitwise XOR
Constant MIR_NOT as Integer is 20013                  Note: Bitwise NOT
Constant MIR_SHL as Integer is 20014                  Note: Shift left
Constant MIR_SHR as Integer is 20015                  Note: Shift right
Constant MIR_SAR as Integer is 20016                  Note: Arithmetic shift right

Note: Comparison Operations (20100-20199)
Constant MIR_EQ as Integer is 20100                   Note: Equal
Constant MIR_NE as Integer is 20101                   Note: Not equal
Constant MIR_LT as Integer is 20102                   Note: Less than
Constant MIR_LE as Integer is 20103                   Note: Less than or equal
Constant MIR_GT as Integer is 20104                   Note: Greater than
Constant MIR_GE as Integer is 20105                   Note: Greater than or equal

Note: Memory Operations (20200-20299)
Constant MIR_LOAD as Integer is 20200                 Note: Load from memory address
Constant MIR_STORE as Integer is 20201                Note: Store to memory address
Constant MIR_ALLOCA as Integer is 20202               Note: Stack allocation
Constant MIR_LOAD_FIELD as Integer is 20203           Note: Load struct/record field
Constant MIR_STORE_FIELD as Integer is 20204          Note: Store struct/record field
Constant MIR_ADDRESS_OF as Integer is 20205           Note: Get address of value
Constant MIR_DEREF as Integer is 20206                Note: Dereference pointer

Note: Control Flow Operations (20300-20399)
Constant MIR_PHI as Integer is 20300                  Note: SSA phi node (value merging)
Constant MIR_BRANCH as Integer is 20301               Note: Conditional branch
Constant MIR_JUMP as Integer is 20302                 Note: Unconditional jump
Constant MIR_RETURN as Integer is 20303               Note: Return from function
Constant MIR_CALL as Integer is 20304                 Note: Direct function call
Constant MIR_CALL_INDIRECT as Integer is 20305        Note: Indirect function call
Constant MIR_SWITCH as Integer is 20306               Note: Multi-way branch (switch/match)

Note: Type Operations (20400-20499)
Constant MIR_CAST as Integer is 20400                 Note: Type cast
Constant MIR_BITCAST as Integer is 20401              Note: Bitcast (reinterpret bits)
Constant MIR_TRUNC as Integer is 20402                Note: Truncate to smaller type
Constant MIR_EXTEND as Integer is 20403               Note: Extend to larger type (sign-extend)
Constant MIR_ZEXT as Integer is 20404                 Note: Zero-extend
Constant MIR_FLOAT_TO_INT as Integer is 20405         Note: Float to integer conversion
Constant MIR_INT_TO_FLOAT as Integer is 20406         Note: Integer to float conversion
Constant MIR_PTR_TO_INT as Integer is 20407           Note: Pointer to integer conversion
Constant MIR_INT_TO_PTR as Integer is 20408           Note: Integer to pointer conversion

Note: Atomic Operations (20500-20599)
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_LOAD as Integer is 20500          Note: Atomic load with memory ordering
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_STORE as Integer is 20501         Note: Atomic store with memory ordering
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_EXCHANGE as Integer is 20502      Note: Atomic exchange (swap)
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_CAS as Integer is 20503           Note: Compare-and-swap
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_ADD as Integer is 20504           Note: Atomic fetch-and-add
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_SUB as Integer is 20505           Note: Atomic fetch-and-sub
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_AND as Integer is 20506           Note: Atomic fetch-and-AND
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_OR as Integer is 20507            Note: Atomic fetch-and-OR
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_XOR as Integer is 20508           Note: Atomic fetch-and-XOR
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_MIN as Integer is 20509           Note: Atomic fetch-and-min
Constant MIR_ATOMIC_MAX as Integer is 20510           Note: Atomic fetch-and-max
Constant MIR_FENCE as Integer is 20511                Note: Memory fence/barrier

Note: Vector/SIMD Operations (20600-20699)
Constant MIR_VECTOR_ADD as Integer is 20600           Note: Vector addition
Constant MIR_VECTOR_SUB as Integer is 20601           Note: Vector subtraction
Constant MIR_VECTOR_MUL as Integer is 20602           Note: Vector multiplication
Constant MIR_VECTOR_DIV as Integer is 20603           Note: Vector division
Constant MIR_VECTOR_FMA as Integer is 20604           Note: Vector fused multiply-add
Constant MIR_VECTOR_MIN as Integer is 20605           Note: Vector minimum
Constant MIR_VECTOR_MAX as Integer is 20606           Note: Vector maximum
Constant MIR_VECTOR_ABS as Integer is 20607           Note: Vector absolute value
Constant MIR_VECTOR_NEG as Integer is 20608           Note: Vector negation
Constant MIR_VECTOR_SQRT as Integer is 20609          Note: Vector square root
Constant MIR_VECTOR_LOAD as Integer is 20610          Note: Vector load from memory
Constant MIR_VECTOR_STORE as Integer is 20611         Note: Vector store to memory
Constant MIR_VECTOR_SHUFFLE as Integer is 20612       Note: Vector shuffle/permute
Constant MIR_VECTOR_EXTRACT as Integer is 20613       Note: Extract scalar from vector
Constant MIR_VECTOR_INSERT as Integer is 20614        Note: Insert scalar into vector
Constant MIR_VECTOR_BROADCAST as Integer is 20615     Note: Broadcast scalar to vector
Constant MIR_VECTOR_REDUCE_ADD as Integer is 20616    Note: Horizontal add reduction
Constant MIR_VECTOR_REDUCE_MUL as Integer is 20617    Note: Horizontal multiply reduction
